<subSubSection pageId="88" pageNumber="89" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="88.[151,1437,613,1288]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[268,503,901,928]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" pagination="54 - 70" refId="ref371107" refString="Rondani, C. (1876 a) Repertorio degli insetti parassiti e delle loro vittime. Supplemento alla Parte Prima [part]. Bullettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 8 (1), 54 - 70." type="journal article" year="1876">Rondani (1876a: 64)</bibRefCitation>
included enough characters in his original description to allow us to separate this nominal species from 
<taxonomicName authority="Macquart, 1835" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1835" box="[443,972,937,964]" class="Insecta" family="Milichiidae" genus="Madiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficornis" subGenus="Siphonella">
<emphasis box="[443,527,937,963]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Madiza</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[542,662,937,963]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Siphonella</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[677,787,937,963]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">ruficornis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Macquart, P. - J. - M." box="[793,972,937,964]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" refId="ref357717" refString="Macquart, P. - J. - M. (1835) Histoire naturelle des Insectes. Dipteres. Tome deuxieme. N. E. Roret, Paris, 703 + 2 pp., 12 pls. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 14274" type="book" year="1835">Macquart, 1835</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The MZUF did not contain any specimen named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1876" box="[281,435,973,999]" class="Insecta" family="Milichiidae" genus="Madiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fabae">
<emphasis box="[281,435,973,999]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Madiza fabae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but, under the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1835" box="[673,874,973,999]" class="Insecta" family="Milichiidae" genus="Madiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficornis">
<emphasis box="[673,874,973,999]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Madiza ruficornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, there are 
<specimenCount box="[994,1174,973,999]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
labeled “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">
in caule 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Vicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fabae">Vicia fabae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
[in a 
<taxonomicName box="[327,453,1009,1035]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Vicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fabae">
<emphasis box="[327,453,1009,1035]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Vicia fabae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
stem]”. In our opinion, these could be the 
<typeStatus box="[933,1031,1010,1036]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">syntypes</typeStatus>
for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1876" box="[1078,1232,1009,1035]" class="Insecta" family="Milichiidae" genus="Madiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fabae">
<emphasis box="[1078,1232,1009,1035]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Madiza fabae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. An additional female in the MZUF numbered “2051” and labeled “ 
<emphasis box="[760,1134,1045,1071]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1835" box="[760,906,1045,1071]" class="Insecta" family="Milichiidae" genus="Madiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficornis">M. ruficornis</taxonomicName>
in tipica 
<taxonomicName box="[1009,1134,1045,1071]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Vicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fabae">Vicia fabae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
” is not included in the type series because its label is yellowish rather than the greenish color of Rondani’s original handwritten ones and is in a lower row in the Box: we treat it to be a subsequent addition. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[921,1108,1117,1144]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" pagination="54 - 70" refId="ref371107" refString="Rondani, C. (1876 a) Repertorio degli insetti parassiti e delle loro vittime. Supplemento alla Parte Prima [part]. Bullettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 8 (1), 54 - 70." type="journal article" year="1876">Rondani (1876a)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1876" box="[1216,1368,1117,1143]" class="Insecta" family="Milichiidae" genus="Madiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fabae">
<emphasis box="[1216,1368,1117,1143]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Madiza fabae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the family 
<taxonomicName box="[279,421,1153,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chloropidae</taxonomicName>
. Nowadays the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Fallen, 1810" authorityName="Fallen" authorityYear="1810" box="[670,901,1153,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Milichiidae" genus="Madiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[670,754,1153,1179]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Madiza</emphasis>
Fallén, 1810
</taxonomicName>
is included in the family 
<taxonomicName authority="(Evenhuis &amp; Pape 2020)" baseAuthorityName="Evenhuis &amp; Pape" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Milichiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Milichiidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Pape, T." pageId="88" pageNumber="89" refId="ref350035" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Pape, T. (2020) Systema Dipterorum. Version 2. 7. Available from: http: // www. diptera. org / (accessed 30 August 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Evenhuis &amp; Pape 2020</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. However, our study of the type allows us to confirm this nominal species belongs to the family 
<taxonomicName box="[199,340,1225,1251]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chloropidae</taxonomicName>
, as confirmed by the biology of the species (stem-miners) and its label (
<emphasis box="[1134,1254,1225,1251]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Siphonella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Macquart, P. - J. - M." box="[1260,1436,1225,1252]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" refId="ref357717" refString="Macquart, P. - J. - M. (1835) Histoire naturelle des Insectes. Dipteres. Tome deuxieme. N. E. Roret, Paris, 703 + 2 pp., 12 pls. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 14274" type="book" year="1835">Macquart, 1835</bibRefCitation>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName box="[322,466,1261,1288]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chloropidae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
